  "response_text": "The commercial opens on a bright beach beside the ocean. In the foreground, a young blonde woman with windblown hair faces the viewer, smiling. She wears a white T-shirt with a colorful Free Wheelin’ Ford Trucks graphic featuring an orange truck. Behind her, a dark red or maroon pickup is parked on the sand with its tailgate down. Several casually dressed young people sit and lounge in the open bed, barefoot and relaxed, with the water and pale sky behind them. One person wears a sleeveless sports-style shirt with the number 30 on the back.\n\nThe scene changes to a white custom van parked on a street outside a storefront with a large sign reading “Country Kitchen.” The van has bold orange and yellow striping running along its sides and around the rear, giving it a customized look. A person stands near the van on the sidewalk. The image then blends into a white pickup truck with matching orange striping driving slowly through a small commercial area or shopping plaza. The pavement appears dark and wet, reflecting light, and the pickup passes storefronts under a long overhang.\n\nNext, an orange Ford Bronco with a black rear roof section is parked in a sunny, rugged mountain setting. It has decorative striping along the side and off-road tires. Two people stand near the front of the vehicle with rocky hills and distant mountains in the background. The commercial then shows a yellow or tan pickup with orange striping parked on rough ground near dark rock formations. A young woman in an orange top stands near the front while a young man in a plaid shirt and jeans walks beside the truck carrying camping gear, including a large rolled pack on his back and a green duffel-like bag at his side. He turns toward her, and they appear to greet each other or gesture playfully beside the truck.\n\nBack at the beach, the young people are seen close together in the bed of the pickup. Their faces fill the view: the blonde woman in the white shirt, a dark-haired young man, and another young woman in a red sports-style top. Their hair blows in the wind, and they laugh and lean into one another, crowded together in a carefree way.\n\nTheir smiling faces softly overlap with the image of the orange Bronco driving along the shoreline. The Bronco moves across pale sand near the water’s edge, parallel to the ocean. Its side stripe and rear-mounted spare tire are visible. As it continues, the tires throw up sand and sea spray. The vehicle drives into wetter sand near the surf, and a cloud of white spray partially hides it before it emerges farther along the beach.\n\nThe beach group reappears, still laughing and jostling in the pickup bed. The blonde woman’s hair streams across her face as she smiles broadly. The people lean close together, looking at one another and toward the front, with the pickup’s rear window and bed rails behind them.\n\nA wider view reveals the group sitting on the lowered tailgate of a dark maroon flareside pickup with white pinstriped styling on the rear fenders. A young man with dark hair and a moustache, wearing a dark football-style shirt with large white numbers “44” and yellow sleeve stripes, moves forward from the tailgate toward the viewer. Behind him, the others remain clustered on the truck: a curly-haired young man in a blue top sits with a blonde woman hugging him from behind, while more friends lean and laugh at the left side of the tailgate. The man in the “44” shirt faces forward and points directly outward, as if addressing the viewer, while the custom pinstriped truck remains prominently beside him.\n\nThe commercial then focuses tightly on the rear fender of the maroon flareside pickup. The red taillight, curved fender, and white pinstripe outlines are clearly visible. The man’s arm, with the yellow-striped sleeve, moves across the fender as he gestures to the decorative striping and then lays his hand flat on the glossy painted surface, emphasizing the custom look.\n\nInside a customized van, the view looks forward from the rear cargo area. The interior is warm-toned, with tan carpeting covering the floor and walls, pale upholstered seats, and a clean, open layout. A driver sits at the front near the steering wheel, while another person is partly visible on the right side. The van’s interior appears arranged for comfort rather than work, with a roomy, lounge-like feel.\n\nThe final image gathers the Free Wheelin’ Ford truck lineup on a beach overlooking the ocean. Several customized Ford vehicles are parked in a semicircle: the orange Bronco, striped pickups, a dark pickup, a white van with orange and yellow stripes, and a yellow pickup in the foreground. A few people stand among the vehicles. Large colorful text across the top reads “FREE-WHEELIN’,” and bold text near the bottom reads “FORD TRUCKS.” Smaller text underneath says, “Based on 1978 retail deliveries of all Ford Trucks.”",
